  "_meta": {
    "purpose": "Tow-vehicle ratings for the Tow Safety Calculator. Every vehicle models ONE real, popular, properly-equipped 2025 configuration; the four ratings below are taken from that SAME configuration so they are internally coherent. Manufacturers publish a 'max tow' figure and a 'max payload' figure that usually come from DIFFERENT body/axle configs and are explicitly mutually exclusive (Ram and Ford both say so) — we never mix them.",
    "method": {
      "payload": "Each config's published payload. Cross-checks against the SAE identity payload = GVWR - curb weight (verified exact against Toyota and Chevrolet factory tables).",
      "gcwr": "Manufacturer-published GCWR where available; otherwise the SAE J2807 basis: max trailer weight + curb weight + 300 lb occupant allowance (the same relationship Ram/Ford state on their own towing charts). This is conservative — a manufacturer's rated GCWR is equal to or slightly higher.",
      "tongueWeight": "Not stored per vehicle; the calculator models loaded tongue weight as a % of the trailer's loaded weight (10-15%, default 13%), per the conventional travel-trailer rule.",
      "disclaimer": "Representative figures for trip planning, not a substitute for the door-jamb Safety Compliance Certification Label, which is the truth for any specific truck. Real ratings shift with engine, axle ratio, cab/bed, and option content."
    },
    "modelYear": 2025
  },
